When I get an email from JIRA today our instance is configured to import replies in the JIRA ticket. But the sender is not notified automatically unless I have configured a notification scheme in the project. And still someone else from outside the project team could have send me the issue.

This is my expectation: I send an issue via email to a coworker. He answers. I get an email. I answer. He gets an email and so forth including CCs. All communication is neatly documented in the comments of my JIRA issue.

It may be or may not be, that this can somehow be configurable. But it definitely should be the standard. It is an intuitive way of integrating email with JIRA.

